Three of America's biggest sports stars - Peyton Manning, LeBron James and Serena Williams - have been named and shamed as the worst at marketing unhealthy food to kids.

Researchers at Yale University found pro athletes promoted 44 different food or beverage brands during 2010, with 79 percent of those food products being 'energy-dense and nutrient-poor.'

In the drinks market, 93 per cent of the drinks the mega stars put their names to - including sports drinks - received all of their calories from added sugar, authors found.

